events.description: Kali Yuga, the fourth and final yuga of Hinduism, starts with the death of Krishna.
events.html: • 3102 BC – Kali Yuga, the fourth and final yuga of Hinduism, starts with the death of Krishna.[1]

events.description: The Sixth Crusade: Frederick II, Holy Roman Emperor, signs a ten-year truce with al-Kamil, regaining Jerusalem, Nazareth, and Bethlehem with neither military engagements nor support from the papacy.
events.html: • 1229 – The Sixth Crusade: Frederick II, Holy Roman Emperor, signs a ten-year truce[2] with al-Kamil, regaining Jerusalem, Nazareth, and Bethlehem with neither military engagements nor support from the papacy.

events.description: The Battle of Wesenberg is fought between the Livonian Order and Dovmont of Pskov.
events.html: • 1268 – The Battle of Wesenberg is fought between the Livonian Order and Dovmont of Pskov.[3]

events.description: Amda Seyon I, Emperor of Ethiopia begins his campaigns in the southern Muslim provinces.
events.html: • 1332 – Amda Seyon I, Emperor of Ethiopia begins his campaigns in the southern Muslim provinces.

events.description: George, Duke of Clarence, convicted of treason against his older brother Edward IV of England, is executed in private at the Tower of London.
events.html: • 1478 – George, Duke of Clarence, convicted of treason against his older brother Edward IV of England, is executed in private at the Tower of London.

events.description: Eighty Years' War: Off the coast of Cornwall, England, a Spanish fleet intercepts an important Anglo-Dutch merchant convoy of 44 vessels escorted by six warships, destroying or capturing 20 of them.
events.html: • 1637 – Eighty Years' War: Off the coast of Cornwall, England, a Spanish fleet intercepts an important Anglo-Dutch merchant convoy of 44 vessels escorted by six warships, destroying or capturing 20 of them.

events.description: The ballad opera called Flora, or Hob in the Well went down in history as the first opera of any kind to be produced in North America (Charleston, S.C.)
events.html: • 1735 – The ballad opera called Flora, or Hob in the Well went down in history as the first opera of any kind to be produced in North America (Charleston, S.C.)[4]

events.description: Fourth Anglo-Dutch War: Captain Thomas Shirley opens his expedition against Dutch colonial outposts on the Gold Coast of Africa (present-day Ghana).
events.html: • 1781 – Fourth Anglo-Dutch War: Captain Thomas Shirley opens his expedition against Dutch colonial outposts on the Gold Coast of Africa (present-day Ghana).

events.description: Congress passes a law admitting the state of Vermont to the Union, effective 4 March, after that state had existed for 14 years as a de facto independent largely unrecognized state.
events.html: • 1791 – Congress passes a law admitting the state of Vermont to the Union, effective 4 March, after that state had existed for 14 years as a de facto independent largely unrecognized state.

events.description: French Revolutionary Wars: Sir Ralph Abercromby and a fleet of 18 British warships invade Trinidad.
events.html: • 1797 – French Revolutionary Wars: Sir Ralph Abercromby and a fleet of 18 British warships invade Trinidad.

events.description: Napoleonic Wars: The Battle of Montereau.
events.html: • 1814 – Napoleonic Wars: The Battle of Montereau.

events.description: In Montgomery, Alabama, Jefferson Davis is inaugurated as the provisional President of the Confederate States of America.
events.html: • 1861 – In Montgomery, Alabama, Jefferson Davis is inaugurated as the provisional President of the Confederate States of America.

events.description: With Italian unification almost complete, Victor Emmanuel II of Piedmont, Savoy and Sardinia assumes the title of King of Italy.
events.html: • 1861 – With Italian unification almost complete, Victor Emmanuel II of Piedmont, Savoy and Sardinia assumes the title of King of Italy.

events.description: Bulgarian revolutionary leader Vasil Levski is executed by hanging in Sofia by the Ottoman authorities.
events.html: • 1873 – Bulgarian revolutionary leader Vasil Levski is executed by hanging in Sofia by the Ottoman authorities.

events.description: John Tunstall is murdered by outlaw Jesse Evans, sparking the Lincoln County War in Lincoln County, New Mexico.
events.html: • 1878 – John Tunstall is murdered by outlaw Jesse Evans, sparking the Lincoln County War in Lincoln County, New Mexico.

events.description: Adventures of Huckleberry Finn by Mark Twain is published in the United States.
events.html: • 1885 – Adventures of Huckleberry Finn by Mark Twain is published in the United States.

events.description: Second Boer War: Imperial forces suffer their worst single-day loss of life on Bloody Sunday, the first day of the Battle of Paardeberg.
events.html: • 1900 – Second Boer War: Imperial forces suffer their worst single-day loss of life on Bloody Sunday, the first day of the Battle of Paardeberg.

events.description: Édouard de Laveleye forms the Belgian Olympic Committee in Brussels.
events.html: • 1906 – Édouard de Laveleye forms the Belgian Olympic Committee in Brussels.

events.description: The first official flight with airmail takes place from Allahabad, United Provinces, British India (now India), when Henri Pequet, a 23-year-old pilot, delivers 6,500 letters to Naini, about 10 kilometres (6.2 mi) away.
events.html: • 1911 – The first official flight with airmail takes place from Allahabad, United Provinces, British India (now India), when Henri Pequet, a 23-year-old pilot, delivers 6,500 letters to Naini, about 10 kilometres (6.2 mi) away.

entities.name: United Provinces of Agra and Oudh

events.description: U-boat Campaign: The Imperial German Navy institutes unrestricted submarine warfare in the waters around Great Britain and Ireland.
events.html: • 1915 – U-boat Campaign: The Imperial German Navy institutes unrestricted submarine warfare in the waters around Great Britain and Ireland.[5]

events.description: While studying photographs taken in January, Clyde Tombaugh discovers Pluto.
events.html: • 1930 – While studying photographs taken in January, Clyde Tombaugh discovers Pluto.

events.description: Elm Farm Ollie becomes the first cow to fly in a fixed-wing aircraft and also the first cow to be milked in an aircraft.
events.html: • 1930 – Elm Farm Ollie becomes the first cow to fly in a fixed-wing aircraft and also the first cow to be milked in an aircraft.

events.description: The Empire of Japan creates the independent state of Manzhouguo (the obsolete Chinese name for Manchuria) free from the Republic of China and installed former Chinese Emperor Aisin Gioro Puyi as Chief Executive of the State.
events.html: • 1932 – The Empire of Japan creates the independent state of Manzhouguo (the obsolete Chinese name for Manchuria) free from the Republic of China and installed former Chinese Emperor Aisin Gioro Puyi as Chief Executive of the State.

events.description: Second Sino-Japanese War: During the Nanking Massacre, the Nanking Safety Zone International Committee is renamed "Nanking International Rescue Committee", and the safety zone in place for refugees falls apart.
events.html: • 1938 – Second Sino-Japanese War: During the Nanking Massacre, the Nanking Safety Zone International Committee is renamed "Nanking International Rescue Committee", and the safety zone in place for refugees falls apart.

events.description: World War II: The Imperial Japanese Army begins the systematic extermination of perceived hostile elements among the Chinese in Singapore.
events.html: • 1942 – World War II: The Imperial Japanese Army begins the systematic extermination of perceived hostile elements among the Chinese in Singapore.

events.description: World War II: The Nazis arrest the members of the White Rose movement.
events.html: • 1943 – World War II: The Nazis arrest the members of the White Rose movement.

events.description: World War II: Joseph Goebbels delivers his Sportpalast speech.
events.html: • 1943 – World War II: Joseph Goebbels delivers his Sportpalast speech.

events.description: Sailors of the Royal Indian Navy mutiny in Bombay harbour, from where the action spreads throughout the Provinces of British India, involving 78 ships, twenty shore establishments and 20,000 sailors
events.html: • 1946 – Sailors of the Royal Indian Navy mutiny in Bombay harbour, from where the action spreads throughout the Provinces of British India, involving 78 ships, twenty shore establishments and 20,000 sailors

entities.name: Presidencies and provinces of British India

events.description: First Indochina War: The French gain complete control of Hanoi after forcing the Viet Minh to withdraw to mountains.
events.html: • 1947 – First Indochina War: The French gain complete control of Hanoi after forcing the Viet Minh to withdraw to mountains.

events.description: The first Church of Scientology is established in Los Angeles.
events.html: • 1954 – The first Church of Scientology is established in Los Angeles.

events.description: Operation Teapot: Teapot test shot "Wasp" is successfully detonated at the Nevada Test Site with a yield of 1.2 kilotons.  Wasp is the first of fourteen shots in the Teapot series.
events.html: • 1955 – Operation Teapot: Teapot test shot "Wasp" is successfully detonated at the Nevada Test Site with a yield of 1.2 kilotons. Wasp is the first of fourteen shots in the Teapot series.

events.description: Kenyan rebel leader Dedan Kimathi is executed by the British colonial government.
events.html: • 1957 – Kenyan rebel leader Dedan Kimathi is executed by the British colonial government.

events.description: Walter James Bolton becomes the last person legally executed in New Zealand.
events.html: • 1957 – Walter James Bolton becomes the last person legally executed in New Zealand.

events.description: The Gambia becomes independent from the United Kingdom.
events.html: • 1965 – The Gambia becomes independent from the United Kingdom.

events.description: The Chicago Seven are found not guilty of conspiring to incite riots at the 1968 Democratic National Convention.
events.html: • 1970 – The Chicago Seven are found not guilty of conspiring to incite riots at the 1968 Democratic National Convention.

events.description: The California Supreme Court in the case of People v. Anderson, (6 Cal.3d 628) invalidates the state's death penalty and commutes the sentences of all death row inmates to life imprisonment.
events.html: • 1972 – The California Supreme Court in the case of People v. Anderson, (6 Cal.3d 628) invalidates the state's death penalty and commutes the sentences of all death row inmates to life imprisonment.

events.description: The Xinjiang 61st Regiment Farm fire started during Chinese New Year when a firecracker ignited memorial wreaths of the late Mao Zedong, killing 694 personnel. It remains the deadliest fireworks accident in the world.
events.html: • 1977 – The Xinjiang 61st Regiment Farm fire started during Chinese New Year when a firecracker ignited memorial wreaths of the late Mao Zedong, killing 694 personnel.[6][7] It remains the deadliest fireworks accident in the world.

entities.name: Death and state funeral of Mao Zedong
List of fireworks accidents and incidents

events.description: A thousand armed soldiers raid Kalakuta Republic, the commune of Nigerian singer Fela Kuti, leading to the death of Funmilayo Anikulapo Kuti.
events.html: • 1977 – A thousand armed soldiers raid Kalakuta Republic, the commune of Nigerian singer Fela Kuti, leading to the death of Funmilayo Anikulapo Kuti.[8]

events.description: The Space Shuttle Enterprise test vehicle is carried on its maiden "flight" on top of a Boeing 747.
events.html: • 1977 – The Space Shuttle Enterprise test vehicle is carried on its maiden "flight" on top of a Boeing 747.

events.description: Richard Petty wins a then-record sixth Daytona 500 after leaders Donnie Allison and Cale Yarborough crash on the final lap of the first NASCAR race televised live flag-to-flag.
events.html: • 1979 – Richard Petty wins a then-record sixth Daytona 500 after leaders Donnie Allison and Cale Yarborough crash on the final lap of the first NASCAR race televised live flag-to-flag.

events.description: Thirteen people die and one is seriously injured in the Wah Mee massacre in Seattle. It is said to be the largest robbery-motivated mass-murder in U.S. history.
events.html: • 1983 – Thirteen people die and one is seriously injured in the Wah Mee massacre in Seattle. It is said to be the largest robbery-motivated mass-murder in U.S. history.

events.description: The IRA explodes bombs in the early morning at Paddington station and Victoria station in London.
events.html: • 1991 – The IRA explodes bombs in the early morning at Paddington station and Victoria station in London.

entities.name: Victoria station and Paddington station bombings

events.description: FBI agent Robert Hanssen is arrested for spying for the Soviet Union. He is ultimately convicted and sentenced to life imprisonment.
events.html: • 2001 – FBI agent Robert Hanssen is arrested for spying for the Soviet Union. He is ultimately convicted and sentenced to life imprisonment.

events.description: Sampit conflict: Inter-ethnic violence between Dayaks and Madurese breaks out in Sampit, Central Kalimantan, Indonesia, ultimately resulting in more than 500 deaths and 100,000 Madurese displaced from their homes.
events.html: • 2001 – Sampit conflict: Inter-ethnic violence between Dayaks and Madurese breaks out in Sampit, Central Kalimantan, Indonesia, ultimately resulting in more than 500 deaths and 100,000 Madurese displaced from their homes.

events.description: 192 people die when an arsonist sets fire to a subway train in Daegu, South Korea.
events.html: • 2003 – 192 people die when an arsonist sets fire to a subway train in Daegu, South Korea.[9]

events.description: Up to 295 people, including nearly 200 rescue workers, die near Nishapur, Iran, when a runaway freight train carrying sulfur, petrol and fertilizer catches fire and explodes.
events.html: • 2004 – Up to 295 people, including nearly 200 rescue workers, die near Nishapur, Iran, when a runaway freight train carrying sulfur, petrol and fertilizer catches fire and explodes.

events.description: WikiLeaks publishes the first of hundreds of thousands of classified documents disclosed by the soldier now known as Chelsea Manning.
events.html: • 2010 – WikiLeaks publishes the first of hundreds of thousands of classified documents disclosed by the soldier now known as Chelsea Manning.

events.description: Armed robbers steal a haul of diamonds worth $50 million during a raid at Brussels Airport in Belgium.
events.html: • 2013 – Armed robbers steal a haul of diamonds worth $50 million during a raid at Brussels Airport in Belgium.

events.description: At least 76 people are killed and hundreds are injured in clashes between riot police and demonstrators in Kyiv, Ukraine.
events.html: • 2014 – At least 76 people are killed and hundreds are injured in clashes between riot police and demonstrators in Kyiv, Ukraine.

events.description: 66 people die when Iran Aseman Airlines Flight 3704 crashes in the Dena sub-range in the Zagros Mountains of Iran.
events.html: • 2018 – 66 people die when Iran Aseman Airlines Flight 3704 crashes in the Dena sub-range in the Zagros Mountains of Iran.[10]

events.description: Perseverance, a Mars rover designed to explore Jezero crater on Mars, as part of NASA's Mars 2020 mission, lands successfully.
events.html: • 2021 – Perseverance, a Mars rover designed to explore Jezero crater on Mars, as part of NASA's Mars 2020 mission, lands successfully.[11]
